Mizuho’s Research Unit Names Hajime Takata as Chief Economist

-- B y   Y u m i   I k e d a
-- 
2011-07-04T09:01:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/mizuho-s-research-unit-names-hajime-takata-as-chief-economist.html
Mizuho Research Institute Ltd. has
appointed Hajime Takata as its managing executive officer and
chief economist.  Takata, 52, joined Industrial Bank of  Japan  Ltd. in 1982,
before becoming chief strategist at Mizuho Securities Co., a
unit of Japan’s third-biggest financial group. He was the
second-highest ranked bond analyst this year in a survey of
institutional investors by Nikkei Veritas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yumi Ikeda in  Tokyo  at 
 yikeda4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rocky Swift at 
 rswift5@bloomberg.net . 